Markdown is a formatting approach that one can use for GitHub.
There are many Markdown syntax such as headers, emphasis, lists, images, lists and other syntax.

GitHub pages helps create websites to show your projects and share your work with the world
One can use Jekyll to blog using Markdown syntax, and without having to deal with any databases.


There are text formatting toolbars that allow one to format without learning Markdown syntax.
One can interact with other users using features like mentions, issue and PR references.

